<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
	
	<p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
	
	<p n="1-3">Seventeenth year of Kampavarman.</p>
	
	<p n="3-13">
		With the sixteen <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of gold
		that Vasanta Pirāṭṭiyār, the Brahmin <supplied reason="subaudible">spouse</supplied> of 
		...
		gave,
		ninety <foreign>nāḻi</foreign>s of oil 
		<supplied reason="subaudible">are to be provided</supplied>
		...
	</p>
	
	<p n="13-16">
		We have become those who, with this gold,
		<gap reason="lost"/>
		will burn a perpetual lamp.
	</p>
	
	<p n="16-20">
		We have become those who have sacred food-offerings fed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiru-v-a<supplied reason="lost">mirtu ūṭṭu</supplied>vippōm</foreign></supplied>
		<gap reason="lost"/>
		the field of the landowner given for sacred food-offerings.
	</p>
	
	<p n="20-24">
		<gap reason="lost"/>.
		<supplied reason="lost">The feet of he who protect this pious act are</supplied> on my head <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign><supplied reason="lost">eṉ ta</supplied>lai mēl</foreign></supplied>.	
		<gap reason="ellipsis"/>		
	</p>
			
